## Principles

- **Track, don't ignore.** Every known compromise gets a row in Active Debt.
- **Small, continuous payments.** Prefer daily 15-minute cleanups over quarterly refactors.
- **Promote patterns to linters.** When a debt item represents a recurring anti-pattern, encode the fix as a linter rule and resolve the debt.
- **Grade impact honestly.** Use the Quality Score to identify which debt is actually hurting.

## How Agents Should Use This

- Before starting work in a module, check if there's active debt. If your task intersects with a debt item, consider addressing it as part of the work.
- After completing work, check if you introduced new debt. If so, add a row.
- Don't prioritize debt remediation over the current task unless instructed to.

